-- Nordecon Says Fourth-Quarter Loss Narrowed as Costs Decline
-- B y   O t t   U m m e l a s
-- 2012-02-08T15:08:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-08/nordecon-says-fourth-quarter-loss-narrowed-as-costs-decline.html
AS Nordecon,   the second-biggest
publicly traded Baltic builder, said its fourth-quarter loss
narrowed as operating and finance costs decreased.  The net loss fell to 641,000 euros ($850,000) from 5.9
million euros a year earlier, the Tallinn, Estonia-based company
said in a stock exchange filing today. Revenue jumped 91 percent
to 46 million euros, while the cost of goods sold increased 88
percent, Nordecon said.  Other operating costs fell to 13,000 euros from 3.1 million
euros a year earlier, the company said. Finance costs declined
to 194,000 euros from 2 million euros.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ott Ummelas in Tallinn at 
